00:51:03.250 --> 00:51:06.020
enigmatic picture of my
daughter in the field.

00:51:06.020 --> 00:51:10.080
It's sort of her imagining her
consciousness belonging to it.

00:51:10.080 --> 00:51:12.800
And on the other
hand, it's this echo.

00:51:12.800 --> 00:51:16.570
It is kind of canonizing,
or putting her

00:51:16.570 --> 00:51:18.260
into that larger world.

00:51:18.260 --> 00:51:21.430
So one thought I had
about distraction

00:51:21.430 --> 00:51:24.190
is that we just live in
a world where there's

00:51:24.190 --> 00:51:27.730
lots of horizontal
transfers, where you're here,

00:51:27.730 --> 00:51:29.630
but there's a
resonant association.

00:51:29.630 --> 00:51:31.910
There's something else
you're thinking of.

00:51:31.910 --> 00:51:34.340
And do we always want to
call that distraction?

00:51:34.340 --> 00:51:37.750
I mean, that would seem like
a kind of depletion of the way

00:51:37.750 --> 00:51:40.990
in which sometimes
reference in this way,

00:51:40.990 --> 00:51:47.530
or sideways dislocation, or
mental wandering and return,

00:51:47.530 --> 00:51:52.480
that seems like that is actually
part of what we call attention.

00:51:52.480 --> 00:51:56.200
If you're really good at
intertextually collating,

00:51:56.200 --> 00:51:57.850
we call that a
form of attention.

00:51:57.850 --> 00:52:00.850
But it's also a skitter.

00:52:00.850 --> 00:52:03.640
It's a jump away
from your present.

00:52:03.640 --> 00:52:07.810
So that quality of how the
jump away may be actually

00:52:07.810 --> 00:52:10.031
like the higher
form of attention.

00:52:10.031 --> 00:52:10.530
