01:21:45.220 --> 01:21:45.806
I mean.

01:21:45.806 --> 01:21:47.680
Because to follow up on
what you were saying,

01:21:47.680 --> 01:21:51.400
Marina, about that notion
of the multiplicity

01:21:51.400 --> 01:21:54.340
of available things
sort of in the self,

01:21:54.340 --> 01:21:57.310
and how we figure out which are
the things that are actually

01:21:57.310 --> 01:22:00.520
part of the order of
our lives, I really

01:22:00.520 --> 01:22:02.710
love the point you made
about Tristram Shandy, about

01:22:02.710 --> 01:22:06.110
the piling up of stuff, the way
that there's all these episodes

01:22:06.110 --> 01:22:07.570
that just kind of go.

01:22:07.570 --> 01:22:10.250
And I think one of
the things I try

01:22:10.250 --> 01:22:13.030
to argue in the
book about the novel

01:22:13.030 --> 01:22:18.430
is that what defines it, the
novel, is that it is episodic,

01:22:18.430 --> 01:22:21.460
meaning there's a bunch
of things that happen.

01:22:21.460 --> 01:22:23.680
And then the order, like
the narrative sequence

01:22:23.680 --> 01:22:26.452
that pulls it together,
that looks like one thing

01:22:26.452 --> 01:22:27.160
at the beginning.

01:22:27.160 --> 01:22:30.830
But then later, after a bunch
of other episodes have occurred,

01:22:30.830 --> 01:22:33.700
it may turn out that
other of those things

01:22:33.700 --> 01:22:35.090
were more important.

01:22:35.090 --> 01:22:37.930
So in other words, things
that look like distractions,

01:22:37.930 --> 01:22:41.590
detours, like
off-ramps on your life,

01:22:41.590 --> 01:22:42.730
when you look back at them.

01:22:42.730 --> 01:22:44.771
I feel like Middlemarch
is constructed of nothing

01:22:44.771 --> 01:22:45.850
but off-ramps.

01:22:45.850 --> 01:22:48.280
And then in retrospect
it turns out, oh,

01:22:48.280 --> 01:22:50.430
that thing that happened
to Mr. Bulstrode

01:22:50.430 --> 01:22:53.102
20 years before the novel
began, that's actually

01:22:53.102 --> 01:22:54.310
a crucial aspect of his life.

01:22:54.310 --> 01:22:59.780
So in other words, I
think, the artist part

01:22:59.780 --> 01:23:02.360
of narrative artistry is
to say the things that

01:23:02.360 --> 01:23:05.870
look like they might just
have been kind of out there,

01:23:05.870 --> 01:23:08.240
and had nothing to do
with anything else,

01:23:08.240 --> 01:23:10.239
in retrospect there
is an order to them.

01:23:10.239 --> 01:23:11.780
So again, that goes
back to the point

01:23:11.780 --> 01:23:15.200
where things that look
like distraction or detour

01:23:15.200 --> 01:23:18.190
actually turn out to be
part of the mainstream.

